title: Scott Morrison warns Australians to stay home for Easter or risk coronavirus 'horror scenarios'
description: The comments came as the Federal Government prepares to release the details of its coronavirus modelling, which the Prime Minister insists is "theoretical" and not based on Australian cases of the virus.
content:
Updated 
April 07, 2020 14:25:12
Scott Morrison has warned that Australia risks facing coronavirus "horror scenarios" witnessed overseas if physical distancing is abandoned, particularly during the Easter long weekend.
